FBIS3-57166 "drsov015_b_94046" FBIS-SOV-94-015 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Jan 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military Issues Conference on Defense Industry Conversion Begins LD2401100594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0830 GMT 24 Jan 94 LD2401100594 Moscow ITAR-TASS Language: English Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Sergey Ostanin] [Text] Moscow January 24 TASS -- The Russian Government Academy is holding an international conference to discuss the defence industry's conversion to civilian production in the Russian Federation and other countries of the Commonwealth of Independent States. The conference was convened on the initiative of the non- governmental foundation "International Humanitarian Dimension", the Russian Government Academy, the conversion fund attached to the presidium of the Russian Academy of Sciences and some research and producing associations of the Russian Federation. Representatives of the Federal Defence Ministry, scientists, researchers and Russian and foreign business people are taking part in the plenary session of the conference. Its main aim is to establish horizontal links between investors and manufacturers of new products, as well as the centres for the creation of new jobs for former servicemen and their families. The three-day conference will also discuss political aspects of conversion, the role of information in the development of businesses in Russia and other CIS countries.
